<?php
/**
 * Release focus. Possible values:
 * Horde_Release::FOCUS_INITIAL - Initial announcement
 * Horde_Release::FOCUS_MINORFEATURE - Minor feature enhancement
 * Horde_Release::FOCUS_MAJORFEATURE - Major feature enhancement
 * Horde_Release::FOCUS_MINORBUG - Minor bugfixes
 * Horde_Release::FOCUS_MAJORBUG - Major bugfixes
 * Horde_Release::FOCUS_MINORSECURITY - Minor security fixes
 * Horde_Release::FOCUS_MAJORSECURITY - Major security fixes
 * Horde_Release::FOCUS_DOCS - Documentation improvements
 */
$this->notes['fm']['focus'] = 0;

/* Mailing list release notes. */
$this->notes['ml']['changes'] = <<<ML
The Horde Team is pleased to announce the final release of the Horde Groupware
Webmail Edition version 1.2.10.

Horde Groupware Webmail Edition is a free, enterprise ready, browser based
communication suite. Users can read, send and organize email messages with
three different webmail interfaces and manage and share calendars, contacts,
tasks and notes with the standards compliant components from the Horde
Project.

The major changes compared to the Horde Groupware Webmail Edition version 1.2.9
are:
    * Added an experimental new Share SQL driver with better performance.
    * Fixed a minor bug in the iTip attachment viewer.
    * Fixed encoding of vacation message in the maildrop driver.
    * Minor bug fixes and improvements.
    * Added holiday drivers for Australia, Croatia, Finland, Portugal, San
      Marino, and Spain.
    * Updated Brazilian Portuguese, Czech, French, Hungarian, Russian, and
      Spanish translations.
ML;

/* Freshmeat release notes, not more than 600 characters. */
$this->notes['fm']['changes'] = <<<FM
An experimental new Share SQL driver with better performance has been added.
Fixed a minor bug in the iTip attachment viewer.
The encoding of vacation messages in the maildrop driver has been fixed.
Other minor bugfixes and improvements have been made.
Added holiday drivers for Australia, Croatia, Finland, Portugal, San Marino, and Spain.
Updated Brazilian Portuguese, Czech, French, Hungarian, Russian, and Spanish translations.
FM;

$this->notes['name'] = 'Horde Groupware Webmail Edition';
$this->notes['fm']['project'] = 'horde-webmail';
$this->notes['fm']['branch'] = 'Default';
